    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @olegabr,\r\n\r\nAs specified in the ERC, as shown in the tests, and as you saw yourself, an operator CAN definitely send a token. Indeed the `_transfer` function takes a from argument that is the current owner. However, that `from` is not the sender of the transaction. If you check out the [`transferFrom` function ](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fb36326a58f1bf05896014d540ba7190886e5673/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol#L152-L161), you'll see that the operator can send a token from `from` to `to`.\r\n\r\nIf `A` ownes a token `X`, and `B` is approved for it, `B` can perform the transfer to `C` by calling `transferFrom(A, C, X)`",
